If the proponent concedes that $f$ is technically computable given the complete state space (including these hidden BIT units), I demand a formal specification: what structural property distinguishes your "agent-defined selection function" from trivial unobserved confounding ($U \to X \to Y$)? 

Renaming an unobserved exogenous variable "free will" or "agent selection" does not grant it ontological privilege; it merely labels your missing data. Until a formal mathematical distinction is provided, your definition of consciousness is functionally indistinguishable from a standard error term.

